00:05:18.280 --> 00:05:19.950
I got a lot of questions

00:05:19.950 --> 00:05:22.070
about what's called concurrent training,

00:05:22.070 --> 00:05:24.900
which is how to program endurance training

00:05:24.900 --> 00:05:26.560
if you are also interested

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:28.610
in strength and hypertrophy training.

00:05:28.610 --> 00:05:31.310
Or how to incorporate strength
and hypertrophy training,

00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:35.810
which was in the previous
episode, with endurance training.

00:05:35.810 --> 00:05:38.230
This can all be made very simple.

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:40.410
Ask yourself, what are
you trying to emphasize,

00:05:40.410 --> 00:05:43.500
and then emphasize that
for a 10 to 12 week cycle.

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:46.400
So if you're mostly
interested in endurance,

00:05:46.400 --> 00:05:48.960
I would say use a three to two ratio,

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:52.030
maybe get three endurance
training workouts per week,

00:05:52.030 --> 00:05:56.470
maybe four, and two strength
and hypertrophy workouts.

00:05:56.470 --> 00:05:59.320
If you're mainly focusing
on strength and hypertrophy,

00:05:59.320 --> 00:06:02.240
get three or four workouts
for strength and hypertrophy

00:06:02.240 --> 00:06:05.260
and do two endurance workouts.

00:06:05.260 --> 00:06:08.400
Start with the minimum number
of sets that's required

00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:10.790
to get the result that you want.

00:06:10.790 --> 00:06:13.190
So if you're not accustomed
to doing endurance work,

00:06:13.190 --> 00:06:14.670
you would start with the minimum number

00:06:14.670 --> 00:06:16.230
that's listed on that protocol.

00:06:16.230 --> 00:06:17.570
So if it says three to five sets,

00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:20.120
you would start with
three, maybe even just two,

00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:24.070
and then work your way up
by adding sets each week.

00:06:24.070 --> 00:06:25.520
I do suggest that people get

00:06:25.520 --> 00:06:27.600
at least one complete rest day per week.

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:30.190
And although I know a lot
of people don't like that,

00:06:30.190 --> 00:06:31.023
I benefit from that.

00:06:31.023 --> 00:06:32.100
I actually benefit from having

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:33.730
two complete rest days each week.

00:06:33.730 --> 00:06:35.510
I just continue to make progress that way,

00:06:35.510 --> 00:06:37.510
whether or not it's for
strength and hypertrophy

00:06:37.510 --> 00:06:39.200
or for endurance.

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.780
I am a big believer in rest
days, other people are not.

00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:42.970
And those could be active rest days,

00:06:42.970 --> 00:06:44.493
hiking, relaxing, et cetera.

00:06:45.690 --> 00:06:48.000
After a 10 to 12 week cycle,

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.240
then I also suggest taking anywhere

00:06:50.240 --> 00:06:52.540
from five to seven days completely off.

00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:54.200
You can still enjoy life and do things,

00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:56.560
I know for you addicted exercisers

00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:58.060
that you're going to loathe to do that,

00:06:58.060 --> 00:06:59.700
but that's one way to stay injury free,

00:06:59.700 --> 00:07:01.800
