00:38:47.050 --> 00:38:48.920
If it brings light directly to the retina,

00:38:48.920 --> 00:38:50.230
then you will see clearly,

00:38:50.230 --> 00:38:53.230
that should be intuitive why
that makes, why it makes sense.

00:38:53.230 --> 00:38:55.340
So you might say, well,
why would being outside,

00:38:55.340 --> 00:38:56.440
getting this blue light

00:38:56.440 --> 00:39:00.270
or this blue-yellow contrast from sunlight

00:39:00.270 --> 00:39:02.600
actually offset myopia?

00:39:02.600 --> 00:39:05.740
Well, it probably, and I
want to emphasize probably

00:39:05.740 --> 00:39:06.720
has to do with the fact

00:39:06.720 --> 00:39:08.400
that these melanopsin ganglion cells,

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:10.150
these intrinsically
photosensitive ganglion cells,

00:39:10.150 --> 00:39:13.120
are not just responsible for sleep,

00:39:13.120 --> 00:39:15.750
and talking to your circadian
clock, and that sort of thing,

00:39:15.750 --> 00:39:18.380
they also make connections
within the retina.

00:39:18.380 --> 00:39:20.150
They connect to things like,

00:39:20.150 --> 00:39:21.440
this is for the aficionados,

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:24.150
the ciliary body, the iris,

00:39:24.150 --> 00:39:26.790
the muscles and the
structures within the eye

00:39:26.790 --> 00:39:29.040
that actually move the lens

00:39:29.040 --> 00:39:31.950
and allow you to adjust your vision

00:39:31.950 --> 00:39:34.240
to things up close or far away.

00:39:34.240 --> 00:39:38.020
And in doing so, they
increase or improve the health

00:39:38.020 --> 00:39:40.860
of the little tiny muscles within the eye

00:39:40.860 --> 00:39:42.880
that move the lens.

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:46.660
And they probably, again, this
needs a little bit more work,

00:39:46.660 --> 00:39:48.760
in order to really tamp
down the mechanism.

00:39:48.760 --> 00:39:50.000
They're probably also involved

00:39:50.000 --> 00:39:54.140
in bringing growth
factors and blood supply

00:39:54.140 --> 00:39:58.990
to the muscles and to the
neurons that are responsible

00:39:58.990 --> 00:40:02.810
for this focusing
mechanism within the eye.

00:40:02.810 --> 00:40:05.640
So remember, your eye
is an optical device.

00:40:05.640 --> 00:40:07.820
You were born with lenses,
you don't have to use glasses,

00:40:07.820 --> 00:40:10.340
or maybe you do because you
have lenses in your eyes

00:40:10.340 --> 00:40:11.840
and those lenses need to move.

00:40:11.840 --> 00:40:14.233
It's not a rigid lens, like a glass lens.

00:40:14.233 --> 00:40:15.417
It's a dynamic lens,

00:40:15.417 --> 00:40:17.760
and it has little muscles that pull on it,

00:40:17.760 --> 00:40:21.440
and squeeze it, and make
it thicker or thinner,

00:40:21.440 --> 00:40:23.290
as you look at things close and far away,

00:40:23.290 --> 00:40:25.270
and I'll describe how
