called the ciliary body move the lens.

00:46:08.660 --> 00:46:10.780
So, when you look far away,

00:46:10.780 --> 00:46:13.320
okay, when you see things far away,

00:46:13.320 --> 00:46:17.950
your lens actually relaxes,
it can flatten out.

00:46:17.950 --> 00:46:18.783
So I want you to think about this.

00:46:18.783 --> 00:46:20.410
When you look far away,

00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:23.750
when it may be anywhere from
like 20 feet away from you

00:46:23.750 --> 00:46:27.990
out to a horizon that's miles
or kilometers away from you,

00:46:27.990 --> 00:46:29.500
the lens can just relax.

00:46:29.500 --> 00:46:31.000
It can flatten out.

00:46:31.000 --> 00:46:33.310
And you'll notice that
it actually is relaxing

00:46:33.310 --> 00:46:35.100
to look at a horizon.

00:46:35.100 --> 00:46:36.860
It's relaxing to look far away.

00:46:36.860 --> 00:46:38.970
Whereas if I look at
something up close to me

00:46:38.970 --> 00:46:41.710
like this pen, or my phone,
or a computer screen,

00:46:41.710 --> 00:46:44.870
or this microphone, it takes effort.

00:46:44.870 --> 00:46:46.470
You'll sense the effort.

00:46:46.470 --> 00:46:48.710
Now, some of that effort
is actually eye movements,

00:46:48.710 --> 00:46:50.380
because you have muscles
that can move your eyes

00:46:50.380 --> 00:46:52.190
within their sockets.

00:46:52.190 --> 00:46:54.480
But a lot of the work, quote unquote,

00:46:54.480 --> 00:46:59.320
is neural work of the muscles
having to move and contract,

00:46:59.320 --> 00:47:02.430
such that the lens actually gets thicker,

00:47:02.430 --> 00:47:05.540
in order to bring the light to the retina

00:47:05.540 --> 00:47:08.260
and not to a location in
front of it or behind it,

00:47:08.260 --> 00:47:10.280
so called accommodation.

00:47:10.280 --> 00:47:12.330
There's also changes in
the size of the pupil,

00:47:12.330 --> 00:47:14.800
as things are closer and
further away from you.

00:47:14.800 --> 00:47:18.360
In fact, there's a simple
way to think about this.

00:47:18.360 --> 00:47:20.960
Healthy pupils are going to dilate

00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:23.560
when you look at something
far away from you.

00:47:23.560 --> 00:47:25.630
Now, when you see
something that excites you

00:47:25.630 --> 00:47:28.240
or stresses you out,
your pupils also get big.

00:47:28.240 --> 00:47:29.323
Your eyes get wide.

00:47:30.990 --> 00:47:33.500
But if you look at something far away,

00:47:33.500 --> 00:47:35.730
your pupils are going to dilate.

00:47:35.730 --> 00:47:38.180
And when you look at things
that are closer to you,

00:47:38.180 --> 00:47:39.120
when you move them up close,

00:47:39.120 --> 00:47:40.660
the pupils are going to shrink.

00:47:40.660 --> 00:47:43.550
That's all part of this
accommodation mechanism.

00:47:43.550 --> 00:47:44.990
Now, you might say,

00:47:44.990 --> 00:47:46.600
why are you telling me
about accommodation?

00:47:46.600 --> 00:47:47.433
This is crazy.

00:47:47.433 --> 00:47:48.280
Why are you telling me about this?

00:47:48.280 --> 00:47:51.740
Well, these days we're
spending a lot of time

00:47:51.740 --> 00:47:54.010
looking at things, mainly
our phones up close,

00:47:54.010 --> 00:47:56.770
and computers up close,
and we are indoors.

00:47:56.770 --> 00:48:00.830
If you are a young person, and
even if you are 25 or older,

00:48:00.830 --> 00:48:02.530
and you are spending a lot of time

00:48:02.530 --> 00:48:04.320
looking at things up close,

00:48:04.320 --> 00:48:08.220
and you are not allowing
your vision to relax.

00:48:08.220 --> 00:48:10.470
In other words, you are
not giving your lens

00:48:10.470 --> 00:48:11.840
the opportunity to flatten out,

00:48:11.840 --> 00:48:15.083
and for these muscles to
relieve themselves of this work,

00:48:15.990 --> 00:48:17.780
you may or may not have
migraine headaches.

00:48:17.780 --> 00:48:19.810
You may or may not have headaches.

00:48:19.810 --> 00:48:22.650
You might, and that could
be the cause of those.

00:48:22.650 --> 00:48:27.120
But you are also training your eyes

00:48:28.130 --> 00:48:32.910
to be good at looking at things
up close and not far away,

00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:33.970
and as a consequence,

00:48:33.970 --> 00:48:37.240
you are reshaping the neural
circuitry in your brain,

00:48:37.240 --> 00:48:38.870
and it is not good.

00:48:38.870 --> 00:48:43.660
It is not healthy to only
look at things up close.

00:48:43.660 --> 00:48:45.820
Now, there are a lot of
recommendations out there right now,

00:48:45.820 --> 00:48:47.470
especially with all the lockdowns

00:48:47.470 --> 00:48:49.610
of the last, you know, 12 to 18 months

00:48:49.610 --> 00:48:51.620
that people should look up from
Zoom every once in a while.

00:48:51.620 --> 00:48:53.750
Or maybe now, I'm hearing
that people should take calls

00:48:53.750 --> 00:48:55.060
instead of doing Zoom,

00:48:55.060 --> 00:48:56.630
where you should look up
from your computer screen.

00:48:56.630 --> 00:48:59.720
It's actually not going
to solve the problem,

00:48:59.720 --> 00:49:01.640
just to look up from your computer screen.

00:49:01.640 --> 00:49:02.890
You need to go to a window.

00:49:02.890 --> 00:49:05.450
You need to look out at a distance.

00:49:05.450 --> 00:49:08.150
Ideally, you would even open the window,

00:49:08.150 --> 00:49:10.520
because those windows actually filter out

00:49:10.520 --> 00:49:13.420
a lot of the blue light that
you want during the daytime.

00:49:13.420 --> 00:49:14.550
A lot of the sunlight,

00:49:14.550 --> 00:49:17.150
it's actually 50 times less gets through.

00:49:17.150 --> 00:49:18.490
You want to get out onto a balcony.

00:49:18.490 --> 00:49:21.570
You want to relax your eyes
and look out at the horizon.

00:49:21.570 --> 00:49:23.480
You want to go into what's
called panoramic vision,

00:49:23.480 --> 00:49:25.030
and let your vision expand.

00:49:25.030 --> 00:49:28.310
You want this lens mechanism
to be very elastic.

00:49:28.310 --> 00:49:30.080
You don't want it to get stuck

00:49:30.080 --> 00:49:32.330
in that configuration of
looking at things up close.

00:49:32.330 --> 00:49:35.300
Accommodation is a wonderful
feature of your visual system,

00:49:35.300 --> 00:49:38.200
but you don't want to push that too hard,

00:49:38.200 --> 00:49:40.673
too often, or for too long.

00:49:41.850 --> 00:49:44.050
You want to view the horizon.

00:49:44.050 --> 00:49:45.360
You want to get outside,

00:49:45.360 --> 00:49:48.770
not just to lighten the load on your mind,

00:49:48.770 --> 00:49:50.020
or to think about other things,

00:49:50.020 --> 00:49:54.300
but to maintain the health
of your visual system.

00:49:54.300 --> 00:49:58.780
In other words, you want
to exercise these muscles

00:49:58.780 --> 00:50:02.170
and that involves both the lens moving

00:50:02.170 --> 00:50:05.670
and getting kind of thicker
and relaxing that lens.

00:50:05.670 --> 00:50:06.960
And the relaxation of the lens

00:50:06.960 --> 00:50:08.590
is actually one of the
best things you can do

00:50:08.590 --> 00:50:10.970
for the musculature of the inner eye.

00:50:10.970 --> 00:50:14.960
So what's the protocol, how
often should you do this?

00:50:14.960 --> 00:50:15.840
You might be surprised,

00:50:15.840 --> 00:50:19.090
but for every 30 minutes of focused work,

00:50:19.090 --> 00:50:21.230
you probably want to look
up every once in a while

00:50:21.230 --> 00:50:23.240
and just try and relax
your face and eye muscles,

00:50:23.240 --> 00:50:24.470
including your jaw muscles,

00:50:24.470 --> 00:50:27.780
because all these things are
closely linked in the brainstem

00:50:27.780 --> 00:50:30.610
and allow your eyes to go into
a so-called panoramic vision,

00:50:30.610 --> 00:50:32.360
where you're just not
really focusing on anything

00:50:32.360 --> 00:50:34.840
and then refocus on your work.

00:50:34.840 --> 00:50:39.840
At least every 90 minutes of
looking at things up close,

00:50:40.710 --> 00:50:42.790
or even if you're looking at a screen,

00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:43.890
you know, television screen,

00:50:43.890 --> 00:50:47.090
or you're watching a
movie, or you're indoors,

00:50:47.090 --> 00:50:49.180
for every 90 minutes of that,

00:50:49.180 --> 00:50:53.510
you ideally would have at least 20,

00:50:53.510 --> 00:50:57.410
probably more like 30 minutes
of being outside, ideally.

00:50:57.410 --> 00:51:02.107
But if you can't be outside,
of non up-close vision.

00:51:02.107 --> 00:51:03.260
And you might say, that's impossible,

00:51:03.260 --> 00:51:04.340
how am I supposed to do that?

00:51:04.340 --> 00:51:05.980
You know, I'm in an office
or I'm in a building.

00:51:05.980 --> 00:51:09.550
Get to a window, get outside
if you can do it safely,

00:51:09.550 --> 00:51:13.940
get onto a balcony, and
just let your eyes relax.

00:51:13.940 --> 00:51:17.143
Many people are experiencing
severe vision problems,

